                          "content": "ZeroClaw is Rust — smaller footprint, stronger sandbox (seatbelt/bubblewrap). OpenClaw is TypeScript — much larger plugin/skill library via npm.\n\nIf performance & isolation matter: zeroclaw. If you want breadth of integrations out of the box: openclaw. Both handle the same core agent loop.",
                          "lineHeight": 1.55,
                          "fontFamily": "JetBrains Mono",
                          "fontSize": 11,
                          "fontWeight": "normal"
                        }
                      ]
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
